JOHANNESBURG - The Cradle of Humankind is hosting the first display of the new Homo naledi fossils. The exhibition will be the largest collection of ancient fossil hominids ever put on display to the public.It will include the skeleton of Neo, a remarkably complete adult skeleton dubbed one of the greatest fossil finds of the 21st century.READ: Nine need-to-knows about Homo nalediA few weeks ago, scientists revealed the world-famous Homo Naledi likely existed alongside early humans.The exact age of Homo Naledi has been a mystery so far, and a source of controversy since the 2015 announcement of his discovery.The exhibition opens to the public on Thursday.eNCA